Package com.ngrok.services

Class EndpointConfigurations

java.lang.Object
com.ngrok.services.EndpointConfigurations
public class EndpointConfigurations extends Object
Endpoint Configurations are a reusable group of modules that encapsulate how traffic to a domain or address is handled. Endpoint configurations are only applied to Domains and TCP Addresses they have been attached to. See also https://ngrok.com/docs/api#api-endpoint-configurations.

    • update

      public EndpointConfigurations.UpdateCallBuilder update​(String id)
      Updates an endpoint configuration. If a module is not specified in the update, it will not be modified. However, each module configuration that is specified will completely replace the existing value. There is no way to delete an existing module via this API, instead use the delete module API. See also https://ngrok.com/docs/api#api-endpoint-configurations-update.
      Parameters:
      id - unique identifier of this endpoint configuration
      Returns:
      a call builder for this API call
